    screenshot: { label: "Workforce Panel", desc: "Shows all roles with +/- buttons. Summary bar shows Total Population vs Total Assigned. Epoch-locked roles appear grayed out.", visual: ["👥 Population: 24  |  Assigned: 21  |  Unassigned: 3", "🌾 Farmers: 4  [−][+]  → +32 Food/tick", "🪵 Lumberjacks: 3  [−][+]  → +15 Wood/tick", "🔬 Researchers: 3  [−][+]  → +12 TP/tick"] },
    content: `**All Worker Roles**\n\n| Role | Produces | Base Rate |\n|---|---|---|\n| Farmers | Food | 8/tick |\n| Hunters | Food | 3–7/tick random |\n| Fishermen | Food | 6/tick |\n| Lumberjacks | Wood | 5/tick |\n| Quarry Workers | Stone | 4/tick |\n| Miners (Gold) | Gold | 2/tick |\n| Iron Miners | Iron | 3/tick Iron Age+ |\n| Oil Engineers | Oil | 6/tick Industrial+ |\n| Soldiers | Military Power | — |\n| Researchers | Tech Points | variable |\n| Industrial Workers | Manufacturing Index | — |\n| Builders | Construction Speed | — |\n\n**Early Game Priority:**\nFarmers (2–3 per 10 pop) + Lumberjacks (2–3) + 1–2 Researchers. As you grow, shift toward Miners and Industrial Workers.`,
    tips: ["Researchers have diminishing returns above ~5 unless you've built Universities.", "Industrial Workers boost Manufacturing Index which feeds into GDP.", "Builders speed up construction — valuable when mid-project on expensive buildings."]
